***(ID)                            JES2B207
***(SUBSYSTEM)                     JES2
***(DESIGNER)                      D.H.CARTWRIGHT
***(AUTHOR)                        D.H.CARTWRIGHT
*
***(DATE WRITTEN)                  JULY 1977
***(DATE TESTED)                   JULY 1977
***(DATE INSTALLED)                JULY 1977
*
***(ABSTRACT)
*
*        THIS MODIFICATION WAS WRITTEN AS PART OF THE BENCHMARK
*        / TUNING EXERCISE CARRIED OUT IN COOPERATION WITH LOU
*        DELURGIO OF IBM ST.LOUIS.THE IDEA WAS TO RUN MVS AS A VIRTUAL
*        MACHINE UNDER VM BUT TO RUN ALL JOBS AS 'REAL'.
*        TO ACHIEVE THIS 'ADDRSPC=REAL' WAS ADDED TO ALL JOB CARDS.
*
*        THE DESIRED PERFORMANCE OBJECTIVES WERE NOT ACHIEVED AND
*        THE MODIFICATION WAS SHELVED.
*
***(LOGIC SUMMARY)
*
*        THIS MODIFICATION IS AN EXIT IN THE CONVERTER JOB CARD
*        PROCESSING ROUTINES TO ADD EXTRA TEXT TO THE CONVERTED
*        JOB CARD AFTER ALL OTHER PROCESSING.
*
***(INSTALLATION)
*
*        THIS IS A MONSANTO JES2 MOD DYNAMICALLY LOADED AT
*        INITIALISATION TIME UPON REQUEST VIA AN 'EXIT=' CONTROL CARD.
*
***(TESTING)
*
*        THE MOIFICATION WAS TESTED DURING BENCHMARKING AND
*        WAS ASSUMED TO BE WORKING BECAUSE OF THE LARGE NUMBER
*        OF MESSAGES CONCERNING JOBS WAITING FOR V=R AREA.
*
